# No en dash or em dash

Do not use the en dash (`–`, U+2013) or em dash (`—`, U+2014) in user-facing copy, Markdown, comments, or strings.

Use instead:

- ASCII hyphen-minus (`-`), often with spaces: `one - two`
- A colon after a label: `**Label**: detail`
- Commas or parentheses for appositives or asides

```markdown
<!-- Bad -->
Topics — methods and results

<!-- Good -->
Topics: methods and results
Topics - methods and results
```

Hyphenated compounds and minus signs in code (`a - b`, `file-name`) are fine.
